Senior Pastor of Solid Kingdom Church, Apostle John Okoriko has admonished Nigerians to shun laziness and embrace hard work with due diligence to any given assignment as the only way to make honest wealth. The clergy insisted that despite the economic climate in the country, the resort to ritual sacrifice of human parts for money was as a result of ignorance and plain stupidity. Apostle Okoriko was reacting to the recent story that went viral of a man and his mother that killed the son’s girlfriend and ate her heart for ritual money as advised by a “pastor”. He said “Let me use this medium to enlighten Nigerians that this is a function of total ignorance on the part of the pastor and stupidity on the part of the mother and son. Nobody has ever made money through ritual sacrifice of human parts. “Money is a product of hard work and sustained investment. No human parts can vomit money for anyone. It has never happened and would never happen. “Laziness is the reason people hoped to make money through ritual sacrifice not through hard work and sustained investment. The bible say it is God that gives a man the power to make wealth. Deut 8:18 and also says: seeing a man diligent in his business, he shall stand before king’s and not before mean men. “I advise Nigerians to shun laziness that breeds the ignorance of seeking money through ritual sacrifice and embrace hardwork and diligence to maximise wealth.” The clergy stressed.